### Description


This is for all ST targets and tool chains. To reproduce initialize a SPI peripheral with a valid ssel pin then call the write function. The program will hang in an infinite loop in the write function call. For instance:

```

SPI spi(SPI_MOSI, SPI_MISO, SPI_SCK, SPI_CS);

int main() {
	spi.format(8, 0);
	spi.frequency(2000000);
	spi.write(0xAA);//infinite loop stm_spi_api.c line 407
	while (1) {
	}
}
```

The issue is fixed by adding the following below stm_spi_api.c line 165
```
    if (ssel != NC) {
        pinmap_pinout(ssel, PinMap_SPI_SSEL);
        handle->Init.NSS = SPI_NSS_HARD_OUTPUT;
    } else {
        handle->Init.NSS = SPI_NSS_SOFT;
    }
```
The hardware NSS line is meant more for a multi-master configuration than for addressing slave devices. ST forum discussion on the subject:

https://community.st.com/thread/39153-spi-master-nss-always-low-in-stm32f4

I would recommend the code be improved by always initializing the SPI peripheral to software NSS and using LL driver calls to toggle the NSS pin if one has been specified. This will make the SPI behavior match what the user expects when specifying a NSS pin.

